rge VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Goodwyn was born in 1480, in Nayland, Suffolk, England. She had at least 1 son with David Abbes. She died in 1523, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1480–1523":"1480–1523","1450–1543":"1450–1543","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1554":"1554","1543":"1543","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1480–1523":"1480–1523","1450–1543":"1450–1543","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1554":"1554","1543":"1543","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1480–1523":"1480–1523","1450–1543":"1450–1543","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1554":"1554","1543":"1543","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Goodwyn est née en 1480, à Nayland, Suffolk, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec David Abbes. Elle est décédée en 1523, à l’âge de 43 ans."},"de":{"1480–1523":"1480–1523","1450–1543":"1450–1543","1495–1554":"1495–1554","1523":"1523","1554":"1554","1543":"1543","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Nayland, Suffolk, England","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Goodwyn wurde 1480 in Nayland, Suffolk, England geb